results.name: Decimal expansion of Gamma(1/6).
comment: A175379 * A073005 * A002161 * A073006 * A203145 = 4*sqrt(Pi^5/3), which is the case n=6 of Product_{i=1..n-1} Gamma(i/n) = sqrt((2*Pi)^(n-1)/n). - _Bruno Berselli_, Dec 18 2012
The transcendence of this constant is in the mathematical folklore; see Finch (who credits Nesterenko) and Gun-Murty-Rath. - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Nov 11 2013
